<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-307-768  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 307 768  OV: 08 307 718.andO; </DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  April 2 1990 v12 n14 p54(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tandon Personal Data Pac. (Software Review) (one of sevenevaluations of removable disk drives in 'You CAN take it withyou.') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Slovick, Linda; Banapour, Zoren.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Tandon Corp's Personal Data Pac removable hard disk drive consistsof a sealed two-platter Winchester drive and an 'Ad-Pac'receptacle into which the drive is inserted.andP;  The Ad-Pac sells for$580, while the Data Pac units are $539 each.andP;  Performance onbenchmark tests and on random-access and backup tests isexcellent.andP;  Documentation is good, but ease of setup is poorbecause the Data Pac performs erratically when formatted undersome non-Tandon DOS versions.andP;  The company recommends eitherTandon MS-DOS or IBM PC-DOS.andP;  Ease of use is good .andP;  The Tandonbehaves like a conventional hard disk once formatted, and userscan back up a working Pac to an archive unit.andP;  Workmanship issatisfactory.andP;  Tandon sells the Personal Data Pac through dealers;its support policies are satisfactory.andP;  Technical support is verygood, and the Personal Data Pac is rated a very good value.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tandon Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Tandon Personal Data Pac (Removable hard disk drive).andO;Topic:     Removable DiskEvaluationDisk DrivesComparison.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>